osport-world-star-of-the-year |publisher=Real Madrid Club de F\u00fatbol |website=Realmadrid.com |accessdate=22 January 2017 |quote=Cristiano Ronaldo has been chosen as the World Star of the Year in the popular vote by the users of the sports television channel Eurosport. |location=Madrid, Spain }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[European Sportsperson of the Year]]\n|2016{{efn|The first time a football player has been awarded the prize.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.as.com/en/2016/12/27/football/1482823059_009875.html |title=Cristiano Ronaldo: European Sportsperson of 2016 |work=Diario AS |date=27 December 2016 |accessdate=7 April 2017 |last=Ruiz |first=Marco |quote=27 Euro media agencies have selected the Real Madrid striker as their sportsperson of the year, the first time a football player has been awarded the prize.}}</ref>}} and 2017\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{cite news |title=Cristiano Ronaldo named as the European Sportsperson of the Year |url=http://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2016/12/cristiano-ronaldo-named-as-the-european-sportsperson-of-the-year |publisher=Real Madrid Club de F\u00fatbol |website=Realmadrid.com |accessdate=7 April 2017 |quote=The Real Madrid striker has been voted the European Sportsperson of 2016 by 27 international news agencies. |location=Madrid, Spain |date=27 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2017/12/cristiano-ronaldo-voted-best-european-sportsperson-of-2017|title=Cristiano Ronaldo, voted Best European Sportsperson of 2017 |website=Realmadrid.com |date=28 December 2017 |accessdate=29 December 2017 |quote=The Portuguese forward received this recognition, awarded by international news agencies, for the second year in a row. |publisher=Real Madrid Club de F\u00fatbol |location=Madrid, Spain}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Sky Sports]]' Sportsperson of the decade\n|2010s\n|{{won|Third place|color=\\#99FFFF}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|first1=James|last1=Dielhenn|first2=Nick|last2=Wright|first3=Adam|last3=Bate|first4=Mark|last4=Hughes|first5=Raz|la