o]], [[Portugal]]|first=Carlos|last=Machado}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[2019 Supercoppa Italiana|2019]]\n|bgcolor=\"#DCE5E5\"|[[Supercoppa Italiana]] runner-up{{efn|name=L}}\n|Juventus\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.uk/cristiano-ronaldo-quickly-takes-off-his-silver-medal-after-juventus-loses-italian-super-cup-1673542|title=Cristiano Ronaldo quickly takes off his silver medal after Juventus loses Italian Super Cup|date=23 December 2019|access-date=27 January 2020|work=[[International Business Times]]|first=Aakash|last=Chatterjee}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://www.espn.com.ec/video/clip/_/id/6452446|title=Cristiano no aguant\u00f3 la bronca y se sac\u00f3 la medalla de subcampe\u00f3n|trans-title=Cristiano did not hold back his anger and removed his runners-up medal|language=Spanish|date=22 December 2019|access-date=23 December 2019|publisher=ESPN|medium=News clip|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191225202610/https://www.espn.com.ec/video/clip/_/id/6452446|archive-date=25 December 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==== Friendly competitions ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" width=5%|Year\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14%;\"|Competition\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10%;\"|Club / national team\n! scope=\"col\" width=5%|Ref(s)\n|-\n|2003\n|[[Toulon Tournament]]{{efn|Ronaldo was a squad member, as Portugal won the tournament.}}\n|Portugal\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/m/man_utd/3144881.stm |title=Ronaldo set to shine |date=12 August 2003 |accessdate=21 January 2017 | work=BBC Sport |quote =Both Inter Milan and Liverpool have been linked with 'the other' Ronaldo, who was watched by Liverpool at the Toulon tournament this summer.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablest/toulon03.html |title=Tournoi Espoirs de Toulon 2003 |date=19 June 2004 |accessdate=21 January 2017 |last=Garin |first=Erik |quote=Final [June 21, Stade Mayol in Toulon] Portugal 