/2019, 4/2019, 12/2019, and 1/2020\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2018/mvp-of-the-month--the-winner-is----cristiano-ronaldo.php|title=MVP of the Month: the winner is... Cristiano!|website=Juventus.com|date=29 September 2018|accessdate=20 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2018/cristiano-ronaldo-awarded-mvp-of-the-month-before-juve-genoa.php|title=Ronaldo awarded MVP of the Month before Juve-Genoa|website=Juventus.com|date=20 October 2018|accessdate=4 January 2019|quote=Ronaldo was named as the best player for the month of September, as voted by the fans on Juventus.com, and is the first Bianconero to win the prize this season.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2018/ronaldo-voted-the-best-bianconero-for-november.php|title=Ronaldo voted the best Bianconero for November|website=Juventus.com|date=6 December 2018|accessdate=4 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2019/cristiano-ronaldo-wins-juventus-mvp-award-for-december.php|title=Ronaldo wins MVP award for December!|website=Juventus.com|date=19 January 2019|accessdate=23 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2019/mvp-march-cristiano-ronaldo.php|title=March MVP: Ronaldo gets the most votes!|website=Juventus.com|date=19 April 2019|accessdate=20 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2019/mvp-april-cristiano-ronaldo.php|title=MVP: April belongs to Ronaldo|website=Juventus.com|date=3 May 2019|accessdate=4 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2020/mvp--cristiano-wins-december-mvp.php|title=MVP {{!}}Cristiano gets the most votes for December!|website=Juventus.com|date=17 January 2020|accessdate=17 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2020/mvp-january-ronaldo-cristiano.php|title=CR7 is January's MVP|website=Juventus.com|date=1 February 2020|accessdate=2 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Goal (website)|Goal]]'' Juventus' Player of the Season\n|[[2018\u201319 Serie A|2018\u201319]]\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/who-is-juventus-player-of-the-season/h108hokfd187133d47q5kc5ta|title=Who is Juventus' Player of the Season?|work=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|first=Mark|last=Doyle|date=20 May 2019|accessdate=23 May 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n====Friendly competition====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" width=20%|Award\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:13%;\"|Edition / year\n! scope=\"col\" width=5%|Result\n! scope=\"col\" width=5%|Ref(s)\n|-\n|[[International Champions Cup]] Best Player\n|2013\n|{{won}}\n|{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}}\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Goalscoring ===\n==== European Golden Shoe ====\n{{See also|European Golden Shoe}}\nThe European Golden Shoe is awarded to the top goalscorer in [[UEFA|Europe]]. It is awarded based on a weighted points system that allows players in tougher leagues to win even if they score fewer goals than a player in a weaker league. Goals scored in the top five leagues according to the [[UEFA coefficients]] rankings are multiplied by a factor of two, and goals scored in the leagues ranked six to 21 are multiplied by 1.5.\n\nSince the points system was established in 1996, Ronaldo and [[Lionel Messi]] are two of only four players, along with [[M\u00e1rio Jardel]] and [[Luis Su\u00e1rez]], to score 80 or more points.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eusm.eu/item/goldenshoe_winners.htm |title=European Golden Shoe |publisher=European Sports Media |accessdate=20 November 2014}}</ref> Messi was the first player to win the award three times, but Ronaldo surpassed him to become the first four-time recipient.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lionel Messi Awarded Golden Shoe for Third Time after 46 La Liga Goals for Barcelona |newspaper=The Independent |date=20 November 2013 |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/european/lionel-messi-awarded-golden-shoe-for-third-time-after-46-la-liga-goals-for-barcelona-8951828.html |accessdate=9 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Cristiano Ronaldo receives record fourth Golden Boot for Real Madrid goals |newspaper=The Guardian |date=13 October 2015 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/oct/13/cristiano-ronaldo-real-madrid-golden-boot |accessdate=13 December 2015}}</ref> By virtue of being the top scorer in Europe, Ronaldo also received the [[Premier League Golden Boot]] and the [[Pichichi Trophy]] in the respective seasons.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/m/man_utd/7401795.stm |title=Ronaldo & Ferguson win top awards |date=14 May 2008 |accessdate=4 January 2015 |work=BBC}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Bravo |first=Luis Javier |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tabless/spantops.html |title=Spain \u2013 List of Topscorers (\"Pichichi\") 1929\u20132014 |date=5 June 2014 |accessdate=4 January 2015 |work=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304084634/http://www.rsssf.com/tabless/spantops.html |archivedate= 4 March 2016 }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%\";\n! scope=\"col\"| Season\n! scope=\"col\"| Goals\n! scope=\"col\"| Points\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|[[2007\u201308 Premier League|2007\u201308]]\n| {{nts|31}}\n| {{nts|62}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|[[2010\u201311 La Liga|2010\u201311]]\n| {{nts|40}}\n| {{nts|80}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[2013\u201314 La Liga|2013\u201314]]{{efn|Shared with [[Luis Su\u00e1rez]] ([[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]]).}}\n| {{nts|31}}\n| {{nts|62}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"| [[2014\u201315 La Liga|2014\u201315]]\n| {{nts|48}}\n| {{nts|96}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==== UEFA Champions League top scorer ====\n{{See also|List of European Cup and UEFA Champions League top scorers#Top scorers by seasons}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%\";\n! scope=\"col\"| Season\n! scope=\"col\"| Goals\n! scope=\"col\"| {{Abbr|Min.|Minutes played}}\n! scope=\"col\"| Minutes-per-goal ratio\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|[[2007\u201308 UEFA Champions League|2007\u201308]]\n| 8\n| 1,062\n| {{#expr:1062/8 round 3}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|[[2012\u201313 UEFA Champions League|2012\u201313]]\n| 12\n| 1,080\n| {{#expr:1080/12 round 3}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|[[2013\u201314 UEFA Champions League|2013\u201314]]\n| 17\n| 993\n| {{#expr:993/17 round 3}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|[[2014\u201315 UEFA Champions League|2014\u201315]]\n| 10{{efn|Shared with [[Neymar]] and [[Lionel Messi]].}}\n| 1,065\n| {{#expr:1065/10 round 3}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|[[2015\u201316 UEFA Champions League|2015\u201316]]\n| 16\n| 1,109\n| {{#expr:1109/16 round 3}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|[[2016\u201317 UEFA Champions League|2016\u201317]]\n| 12\n| 1,200\n| {{#expr:1200/12 round 3}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|[[2017\u201318 UEFA Champions League|2017\u201318]]\n| 15\n| 1,170\n| {{#expr:1170/15 round 3}}\n|-\n|}\n{{small|Source: [[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]],<ref>{{cite web |first1=Roberto |last1=Di Maggio |first2=Roberto |last2=Mamrud |first3=Davide |last3=Rota|first4=Jarek|last4=Owsianski |title=Champions Cup/Champions League Topscorers |publisher=Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation (RSSSF)|date=8 June 2017 |url=http://www.rsssf.com/ec/ec1tops.html |accessdate=2 November 2017}}</ref> [[UEFA]],<ref>{{cite web |title=UEFA Champions League Statistics Handbook 2017/18: Facts and figures |publisher=Union of European Football Associations (UEFA) |page=11 |url=https://www.uefa.com/MultimediaFiles/Download/EuroExperience/competitions/Publications/02/28/56/88/2285688_DOWNLOAD.pdf |accessdate=2 November 2017}}</ref> worldfootball.net<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldfootball.net/top_scorer/champions-league/ |title=Champions League \u00bb Top Scorer |website=worldfootball.net |accessdate=27 May 2018}}</ref>}}\n\n===== All-time =====\n{{For|a comprehensive listing on this topic|List of European Cup and UEFA Champions League top scorers#All-time top scorers}}\nRonaldo is the UEFA Champions league all-time top goalscorer with 128 goals while Lionel Messi is second with 114 to his name.<ref name=WFNET/> The pair had broken each other's record over the course of 2015, after Messi surpassed the previous recordholder, [[Ra\u00fal]], in November 2014.<ref>{{cite web |title=Apoel Nic 0\u20134 Barcelona |publisher=BBC Sport |date=25 November 2015 |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/29363780 |accessdate=10 August 2015}}</ref> Ronaldo opened a gap in the 2015\u201316 season when he became the first player to score double figures in the group stage of the Champions League, setting the record at eleven goals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-champions-mad-mal-ronaldo-free-idUKKBN0TR2OC20151208|title=Ronaldo sets goals record for Champions League group stage|publisher=[[Reuters]]|date=8 December 2015}}</ref>\n{{updated|26 February 2020}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" width=\"1000\" style=\"font-size:95%\";\n! scope=\"col\"| Rank\n! scope=\"col\"| Player\n! scope=\"col\"| Goals\n! scope=\"col\"| Apps\n! scope=\"col\"| Ratio\n! scope=\"col\"| Years\n! scope=\"col\"| Club(s)\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" align=center| 1\n| style=\"text-align: left\" | {{flagathlete|'''Cristiano Ronaldo'''|POR}}\n| align=center| '''128'''{{efn|Ronaldo additionally scored one goal<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2244072.html |title=Lionel Messi and Cristiano Ronaldo goal for goal |website=UEFA.com |accessdate=19 April 2017 |date=18 April 2017 |quote='''Ronaldo''': Debrecen 3-0 (h) 09/08/05, UEFA Champions League third qualifying round |publisher=Union of European Football Associations (UEFA) }}</ref> in four qualification matches.}}\n| align=center| 168\n| align=center| {{#expr:128/168 round 3}}\n| align=center| 2003\u2013present\n| [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]], [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]], and [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]]\n|-