010 FIFA World Cup|2010]], [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014]] and [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018]]{{failed verification|date=July 2018}} editions of the [[FIFA World Cup|World Cup]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2016/06/cristiano-ronaldo-breaks-another-record|title=Cristiano Ronaldo breaks another record|quote=He is the only player in the world who has scored in the last three World Cups and last four Euros... Following his two goals against Hungary, he is the only player to have scored for his national team in the last seven major international tournaments. The madridista forward has made his mark in the 2004, 2008, 2012 and 2016 editions of the Euro; and in the 2006, 2010 and 2014 editions of the World Cup.|website=Realmadrid.com|publisher=Real Madrid Club de F\u00fatbol|date=24 June 2016|location=Madrid, Spain|access-date = 10 July 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|\n|[[List of FIFA World Cup records#Individual|Most FIFA World Cups scored]] in: 4{{efn|Shared with [[Miroslav Klose]], [[Pel\u00e9]], and [[Uwe Seeler]].}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.footballparadise.com/in-pictures-the-four-men-to-have-scored-at-four-world-cups/|title=In pictures: The four men to have scored at four World Cups|work=[[Football Paradise]]|date=16 June 2018|author=Football Paradise staff reporter|access-date=3 July 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Center|[[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018]]}}\n|[[List of FIFA World Cup hat-tricks#Notable World Cup hat-tricks|Oldest player to score a hat-trick at a FIFA World Cup]]: 33 years, 130 days\n|<ref>{{cite tweet |author=OptaJoe |user=OptaJoe |number=1007712437154480129 |date=15 June 2018 |title=33y 130d - Cristiano Ronaldo is the oldest ever player to score a World Cup hat-trick. History. #PORESP #POR #ESP #WorldCup |access-date=16 June 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Center|2011\u201317}}\n|Only player to score more than 50 goals in seven consecutive calendar years\n|{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n|-\n|\n|First player to score in consecutive [[FIFA Club Worl