ie A|2018\u201319]]}}\n|First player to score in seven consecutive away matches in a debut [[Serie A]] season\n|<ref>{{cite web|first=Jen|last=Offord|url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/serie-a/2018-2019/football-news-benched-cristiano-ronaldo-salvages-point-for-10-man-juventus_sto7065504/story.shtml|title=Football news - Benched Cristiano Ronaldo brought on to salvage point for 10 man Juventus|work=Official website of [[Eurosport]]|date=26 December 2018|access-date=4 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Center|[[2019-20 Serie A|2019-20]]}}\n|Most consecutive Serie A matches played scored in: 11{{efn|Shared with [[Gabriel Batistuta]], and [[Fabio Quagliarella]].}}\n|\n|}\n\n=== Portuguese records ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" width=7%|Date\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:45%;\"| Record\n! scope=\"col\" width=5%|Ref\n|-\n|\n|[[Portugal national football team#Most capped players|Portugal's most capped player of all time: 164 caps]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eu-football.info/_players.php?id=159|title=Played for Portugal national team |accessdate=14 November 2019|website=EU-Football.info}}</ref>\n|-\n|\n|[[Portugal national football team#Top goalscorers|Portugal's all-time top goalscorer: 99 goals]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eu-football.info/_scorers.php?id=159|title=Portugal national football team goal scorers|accessdate=14 November 2019|website=EU-Football.info}}</ref>\n|-\n|\n|Most [[List of Portugal national football team hat-tricks|hat-tricks scored for the Portugal national team]]: 9\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eu-football.info/_players.php|title=National football team individual records and stats|website=eu-football.info|access-date=9 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|\n|[[Portugal national football team#Statistics|Most matches played in European Championship finals]]: 21\n|\n|-\n|\n|Most matches played in World Cup finals: 17\n|\n|-\n|\n|Youngest player to reach 100 caps: 27 years, 8 months and 11 days\n|\n|-\n|\n|First Po